Denote 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{N}|N=n$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{n}.$
\end_inset

 The distribution function of 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{n}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F_{Z_{n}}(z)=P(Z_{n}\leq z)=P(X_{1}\leq z,X_{2}\leq z,...,X_{n}\leq z)
\]

\end_inset

since 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{n}$
\end_inset

 is the maximum and 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{n}\leq z$
\end_inset

 is therefore the same as all 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{1},...,X_{n}$
\end_inset

 being smaller than 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset

.
 Now, because of independence and that all 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{k}$
\end_inset

 have same distribution, we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F_{Z_{n}}(z)=\left(F_{X}(z)\right)^{n}.
\]

\end_inset

Taking the derivative of both sides yields
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{Z_{n}}\left(z\right)=n\left(F_{X}\left(z\right)\right)^{n-1}f_{X}\left(z\right).
\]

\end_inset


